Sentence: Thangkerne aherrk-akwernenhe aherrkarle kwerrantye atwerrpe. Ngkwarle therrpere ane tharrkare re kwatherrantye.
Sentence translation: The singing honeyeater sings in the afternoon to make the sun go down. It sucks honey from the honey grevillea and the turkey bush.

Sentence: Akerrke nyartepe thangkerne ngkerte wantakerrertetye arle twerarte tyepetye ilerrantye antywe kwereyenge arle arrewethe, arreyewe theye aperte arrel-arrel-arrenkepe ntyarlkwe warle atheke kwene.
Sentence translation: The naughty bower bird takes everything such as leftovers to his home and puts them there. He starts to decorate around the entrance to his nest and then works his way down to the main part of the nest.

Sentence: Akngkwenelepe aynenke nterrenge arwele arenye kape athe arenye. Thangkerne nyartepe arltere paympelhe errwelenge, kwenengepe rntere-rntere. Thangkerne nyartepe arlpankele anteyane kwarte akake kape akwerrke akakepe anenke arwele ilperele. Nyartepe thangke
Sentence translation: The Major Mitchell's cockatoo eats seeds from trees, plants and grass. It has white feathers and its wings are white over the top, but red or dark pink down the bottom. It lives in the plains and only nests in a tree hollow when it has eggs or babies. Thi

Sentence: Aleterrpeterrpe, nyartepe thangkerne kelye, repe kwake kelye arne arle mpwarenke antywalke arwelele etntete warle repe anteyane. Thangkerne nyartepe intetyeng-intetye akepe kape paympelhe atherre, arnalkepe marlalperre, kape rntere-rntere.
Sentence translation: The rufous whistler is a small bird that makes its small nest in tree branches. This bird has speckled feathers on its head and wings and its breast is yellow and red.

- Masked Woodswallow, Black-faced Woodswallow
alternate_spellings: []
Sentence: Alpantywerle nyartepe thangkerne weye ahene aynewethe. Thangkerne nyartepe artetyele arre anteyane repe aynenke nterrenge kape ngkwerrme kape aytankerne. Yerrampe re errwelaylenke.
Sentence translation: The woodswallow is good to eat. It lives in mulga country. It eats seeds and misletoes and berries that grow on mulga trees. It brings honeyants closer to the surface.

Sentence: Thangkerne amatheng-amathenge atnentye errpwerle arlkepe elpalhapenye. Artnwengele areme ketye amathengele paperte kwere arenke.
Sentence translation: The black-faced cuckoo-shrike has a black throat and a grey body. If children see this bird they might become orphans.

Sentence: Arlpatye thangkerne weye ahene aynewethe. Thangkerne nyartepe atherrk-atherrke iterrtyepe akepe errpwerle rtame. Thangkerne nyartelepe aynenke nterrenge athe kape arwele arenye.
Sentence translation: The ringneck parrot is a bird that is good to eat. It has a green body and a black head. It eats seeds from grass, plants and trees.

Sentence: Arntepepe thangkerne weye ahene aynewethe.  Thangkerne arntepele aynenke nterrenge athe arenye.
Sentence translation: The bronzewing pigeon is good to eat. It eats grass seeds.

Sentence: Thangkerne arrakwer-akwerele ahakeye anthwerrke artntwenke. Arrakwerakwere angkerranenke artety-artetyele.
Sentence translation: The spiny-cheeked honeyeater lets people know when the native currants are ripe. It can be heard singing in mulga country.

Sentence: Arrkarrepe thangkerne pwelerrnge apenye. Thangkerne nyartepe anteyane arwele ilperrele. Arrkarrelepe aynenke wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye atnkwarengele aperrane.
Sentence translation: The barn owl looks like the southern boobook. It lives or nests in tree hollows. It eats animals and insects that come out at night including mice, grasshoppers and other small insects.

Sentence: Arwengerrpe weye malangke. Arwengerrpelepe aynenke perrkaltye, ayepayte arlkerre, arnewetye kape wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye.
Sentence translation: The bush turkey is the nicest meat that can be found in the bush. The bush turkey eats grasshoppers, caterpillars, conkerberries, desert raisins and other little insects.

Sentence: Thangkerne atetherrele aynenke nterrenge athe kape arwele arenye. Atetherrepe anteyane arwele ilperrele, thangkerne nyartepe ahene aynewethe.
Sentence translation: The budgerigar eats seed from grass and plants. This bird lives in tree hollows and it is also good to eat.

Sentence: Aympaympepe thangkerne ahene aynewethe. Thangkerne nyartelepe aynenke perrkaltye kape wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye. Thangkerne nyartepe anteyane ntyarlkwele errwele.
Sentence translation: The yellow-throated miner is good to eat. It lives on grasshoppers and other little insects. This bird lives in a nest which is up in the hanging branches.

Sentence: Thangkerne eleterrekamekamele errwelarle etnherrantye alkerele. Ertntweyane re apwelhe apenye.
Sentence translation: The Australian kestrel hovers high in the sky. It dances like women during initiation ceremonies

Sentence: Etnkwelepe thangkerne ware elpalhapenye kape aherne apenye. Thangkerne nyartepe weye aynewethe, repe aynenke kaperle, perrkaltye kape wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye.
Sentence translation: The kite is a grey and brown bird. It is a meat-eater that eats lizards, grasshoppers and other lizards and insects.

Sentence: Atye arenherre ilekaynewene rntere-rntere akake. Enye kwereyenge rtame, ilekepe. Ilekaynewene rtame re.
Sentence translation: I saw a red-tailed black cockatoo, a male one (with red feathers). Prickles are its tucker. It's a prickle-eater.

Sentence: Ilerepe thangkerne arwengerrpe apenye. Repe aynenke perrkaltye, ayepayte kape wantakerrertetye. Ilere nyartepe thangkerne errpatye.
Sentence translation: The curlew looks a bit like the bush turkey. It eats grasshoppers, grubs and other insects. This bird brings bad luck.

Sentence: Ilpertenyepe thangkerne errpwerle alkenhe intetyeng-intetye arltere kape aherne apenye. Thangkerne nyartepe weye aynewene. Ilpertenyelepe weye kwereyenge alarrenke aherre, arinenge, kaperle, arlewatyerre kape thangkerne kelye-kelye.
Sentence translation: The wedge-tailed eagle is a big black bird with little spots of white and brown. The eagle is a meat-eater which hunts and kills on its own. It eats kangaroos, euro, lizards, goannas and other small birds.

Sentence: Kaperl-kaperle thangkerne nyarte ware elpalhapenye repe athenge re arre artnperr-entweyane kwene. Kaperle-kaperlepe thangkerne kelye aherne apenye, arnalke errpwerle. Thangkerne nyartelepe aynenke perrkaltye kape wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye.
Sentence translation: The Australian pipit is a grey bird that runs in and out through the grass. This bird is brown and has a black chest. It eats grasshoppers and other little insects.

Sentence: Karlartwerreye arenkerne wele artweye arenge enke kngwere angkwarre apewethe.
Sentence translation: If you see this bird you know to go the other way, because this bird is found near kurdaitchas.

Sentence: Thangkerne nharte arntwarenye. Awatnkakerre iterrtyele aynenye.
Sentence translation: The black-tailed native hen is a waterbird. It was eaten in the olden days.

Sentence: Karnawilkere elpaye arenye. Nharte anteyane arwelele. Atnwenthepe kwere ayneyayne arrwekelenyele ilperewe alarreyayne karnawilkwere.
Sentence translation: The cockatiel lives at the creek. It stays in trees. In the early days people ate the cockatiel, killing them in hollow trees.
Admin only notes: No call for this bird yet MC 15/APR/2016

Sentence: Kelelkelelkepe thangkerne ware elpalhapenye kape rntere-rntere. Thangkerne nyartelepe aynenke nterrenge athe arenye kape arwele arenye. Thangkerne nyartepe anteyane arwele ilperele, kape nyartepe weye ahene aynewethe.
Sentence translation: The galah is a grey and pink bird. It eats seed from grass, plants and trees and nests in tree hollows. It is good to eat.

Sentence: Kerrkerlantyepe thangkerne weye aynewene, repe aynenke kaperle, perrkaltye, ayepayte kape wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye. Thangkerne nyartepe iterrtye kape ake errpwerle arnalke arltere.
Sentence translation: This bird is a meat-eater that eats lizards, grasshoppers, caterpillars and other insects. It has a black head and body with a white chest.

Sentence: Kwayekwayepe thangkerne nganke apenye erlwe atherrepe errpwerle.
Sentence translation: The Australian raven looks very similar to the crow but it has black eyes which the crow doesn't have.

Sentence: Kwepalepalepe thangkerne aherne apenye rlterre rntere-rntere. Thangkerne nyartepe ahene aynewethe. Thangkerne nyartelepe aynenke perrkaltye, ayepayte kape wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye.
Sentence translation: The bellbird is a brown bird with a black chest. This bird eats grasshoppers, caterpillars and other little insects.

Sentence: Thangkerne kwerlekwekele ngkenge ntyerrelewepe arntwarle tywengerlenke angkere.
Sentence translation: This bird the diamond dove can show you the way to water when you are thirsty.

Sentence: Kwerte-kwerte nyartepe thangkerne errpwerle kape arne apenye intetyeng-intetye. Thangkerne nyartepe arlpankele arwelele anteyane kape athenge tyampe. Thangkerne nyartelepe aynenke perrkaltye, ayepayte kape nterrenge. Atnkwarengele angkenke 'kwerte-kwerte, kwerte-kwerte, kwerte-kwerte'.
Sentence translation: The nightjar is a black bird with brown spots. This bird lives on the plains or under trees and grass. It eats grasshoppers, caterpillars and seeds. At night it calls 'kwerte-kwerte, kwerte-kwerte, kwerte-kwerte'.

Sentence: Thangkerne lkwarrer-arrpwernenhe elpathenke kwere ahelaytnenkarle wele aynanthe etelarenke arntwe alkenhe rtame re aperninenke.
Sentence translation: When the channel-billed cuckoo is heard calling we know that it will bring big rains.

- Torresian Crow, Little Crow

Sentence: Ngankelepe aynenke weye, rlwene kape wantakerrertetye kwetyengele. Nganke nyartepe anteyane errwele ntyarlkwe kwereyengelke.
Sentence translation: The crow eats just about every food scrap and little things it can find. This bird lives in a nest which is made from twigs, sticks and leaves.

Sentence: Ngimarrepe thangkerne kelye arlkenye kape intetyeng-intetye. Ngimarrelepe aynenke nterrenge kape arntwe kwathenke. Ahepertewepe ngimarrepe arenke makwerle arntwe warle karrarrenke ngewarlengarle ngentye arle. Thangkerne nyartepe ntyarlkwele anteyane, arwelele.
Sentence translation: The zebra finch is a little bird which has spots and stripes. It eats seeds and drinks water. In the summer months you can see the zebra finch in flocks of hundreds gathering to one waterhole. This bird lives in a nest high up in trees which it makes out of grass.

Sentence: Thangkerne ngimarre alarrewenele ngimarre alarrenke. Thangkerne aperte kwerarle aytnelp-aytnterrantye, ilelp-ilenke re aynewethe tyampelke re.
Sentence translation: The Australian hobby kills zebra finches. It only eats birds. It spears them with its beak and grabs them with its claws.

Sentence: Pelkerepe thangkerne ahene aynewethe. Thangkerne nyartelepe aynenke nterrenge athe arenye kape arwele arenye. Pelkere nyartepe ware elpalhapenye, rlterre rntere-rntere kape arrkaylpe akake akenge arlenge.
Sentence translation: The crested pigeon is good to eat. This bird eats seeds from grass and plants. It is a grey bird with red legs and has a crest on its head.

Sentence: Pwelerrngepe thangkerne ware elpalhapenye, rlwe atherrepe alkenhe. Thangkerne nyartepe atnkwarengele aperrane. Pwelerrngelepe aynenke ilkwennge, kape wantakekerretetye kelye-kelye atnkwarenge, aperrane.
Sentence translation: The southern boobook owl is a grey bird with big eyes; it hunts for food at night. This bird eats mice and other little animals and insects that come out at night.

Sentence: Rtwere angkenke awennngarre angenke ketye.
Sentence translation: When the kingfisher sings it's telling you to dig a grave.

Sentence: Therre-therre nyartepe thangkerne kelye errpwerle kwenenge arnalke angkwerrepe arltere. Thangkerne nyartelepe aynenke wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye. Thangkerne nyartepe ntyarlkwele anteyane.
Sentence translation: The willie wagtail is a little black bird with white under its chest. This bird eats grasshoppers and other little insects. Its home is a (hanging) nest up high in the branches.

Sentence: Twetime rartepe errwelenge aperrane, wele arenke rtame kwere iterrtyelepe, 'twetime nharte errwele fly-arrerrane, repe arrere apeke nthepelarte aperrane' mpele. Antenge theye rtame, atnhelengkwepe.
Sentence translation: When we see the black-breasted buzzard flying high in the sky we know that emus are close behind.

Sentence: Tyelkatherathere wentare angkewene ape re, arlpankele arre aperrane.
Sentence translation: The banded lapwing has a noisy call and is seen on the plains.

Sentence: Ilalthewe aherlaynterane tyengayteyayteyele. Tyengayteyayteye errelewe aharlaynterane. Lwematnewethe atherrkenyele.
Sentence translation: The pallid cuckoo tells you when march flies are around. The pallid cuckoo hollers that all the grasses will be green.

Sentence: Tyewaketye nyartepe thangkerne artetyele arre anenke. Thangkerne nyartepe errpwerle kape arltere. Tyewaketyelepe aynenke wantakerrertetye kelye-kelye.
Sentence translation: This is a black and white bird which lives and can be found in the mulga country. This bird eats little insects that lives in mulga area.
